1. Compile by running `./make.sh`.
2. You must be in the `make xsh` environment.
3. You must run `make` on in the uClibc folder
   after entering the `make xsh` environment.
4. You may have to run the following command
   in some of these folders before they will
   build.
```
	./configure --host=arm-linux --prefix=/usr
```
5. It's recommended you place all these folders
   inside of a folder called /ports at the root.
